From 8011c903b9e8a17db147ef8245c711575f191b4c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sam Thursfield <sam.thursfield@codethink.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 12:44:03 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 10/11] FDSDK 26.08: Override renamed `_private` elements

There is a common pattern in FDSDK used when a component
requires multiple elements. This happens when a single repo is built in
one element, then split with `filter` elements. It also happens when
two-stage bootstrapping is needed.

In FDSDK 25.08, all such "base" and "stage1" elements were in the
`components/` directory. In the upcoming FDSDK 26.08 release, these
elements are moved into `components/_private`.

The `_private` naming suggests we shouldn't override them, but there
is currently no other way to achieve customizations such as overriding
the systemd version. (GNOME OS tracks systemd 'main' since
https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-build-meta/-/merge_requests/4647).
